      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">[Nübel] ¶ editorial addition. ¶  ¶ 2nd Dec. 1840. ¶ From the text of the letter the date should read 20 December 1842. The letter was written a week before Iwanne's departure from Nübel which was to b...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">42.12.20</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Iwanne Müller</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Private hands.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. The text given here was 'Translated in Sydney from the German', and placed in Louise Wehl's scrap-book.</p>
               </note>[Nübel]<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>2nd Dec. 1840.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>From the text of the letter the date should read 20 December 1842. The letter was written a week before Iwanne's departure from Nübel which was to be on the Tuesday after Christmas (i.e. 27 December 1842).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Oh! beloved brother soon, only another 8 days and I shall be with you! I am extremely happy in the thought to see you so soon — so unexpectedly. To explain everything by letter would be too long, so shall wait till we meet.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Here everything has become different so therefore I thought it the better plan to pack my things and come over when opportunity offered. Tuesday after Xmas I shall travel by dilligence<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A mail coach running to a regular timetable.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>from here to Heusburg,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Flensburg.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and Wednesday I leave there for Husum. Please dear Ferdinand forward the enclosed letter to Albertine<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Albertine Warder?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the contents of which will not remain strange to you. I also wrote to the Mertens and asked them to let me know how I am to get from Husum to Tonning but that I would like to stay several days in Husum, when we can see one another often, and tell all the news, to which I am looking forward very much.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You were worried that I might be ill, and I was worried about you as you had not written for seven weeks. I waited in vain for a letter, now I am happy for a little while but it does not last long, and I fall back again into my condition of sadness. Oh in this world everything is vain — all earthly things are valueless — only the higher and better has any remaining value for us.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Now I am anxious to know what sort of position uncle will find for me in Hamburg. I dislike the housework so would much sooner do needlework. Please the dear Lord that it will be a nice position, so that I have again a little pleasure in my life. After all one is human and young. So good bye dear boy will see you soon.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Your Iwanne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I only want to remind you not to write here again — your letter might come too late.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Your sister.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The translator has noted below the valediction ‘The address on above letter was destroyed’</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
      </body>
